            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-01-05T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-31T23:30:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Document <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 18/2, February 17, 1949, which was
                    approved by President Truman, set forth a revised policy on economic relations
                    between the United States and Yugoslavia. Telegrams 92, February 25, to
                    Belgrade, repeated to Athens as 256, and 288, March 2, to Athens, repeated to
                    Belgrade as 99, explained the anticipated result of this revised policy on
                    Yugoslav relations with Greece and the Greek guerrillas. Officers of the
                    Department of State also discussed the matter with Greek Ambassador Vassili
                    Dendramis on March 1. The documents identified here are included in <ref target="frus1949v05#pg_854">volume V, pages 854</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
